# Write A Letter To Dixon — mission context

## What this is

Playful and dryly humorous **official diplomatic transmission** from the **Arcturian High Council** to **DJ Dixon**, formally requesting **backstage VIP access** at **DC10 Circoloco Opening Weekend, Ibiza**. 

**Live site:** [writealettertodixon.com](https://writealettertodixon.com)

## Tone and UX

- **Voice:** Diplomatic / classified briefing meets sci-fi camp—sincere fun, not corporate or generic “blog” tone. Dry humour with a german twist would be ideal. Appealing to electronic music fans with a finer taste of electronic music.
- **Visual identity:** Classified document, paper, stamps, mono labels—keep new UI consistent with existing patterns in `app/src` (see `App.css`, document components).
- **Navigation labels:** **Official Letter** (the transmission), **Mission Updates** (relay notices / field reports; route `/mission-updates`), **Dossier** (about/meta). Legacy `/signals` redirects to `/mission-updates`.
- **Does and Don'ts** - do not mention "minimum spam" in any content. always update missions from the arcturian high council, only ever mention the ambassadors in the 3rd person. Only use positive statements, never undermine or demean humans. Humour should be clever, not crass or passive aggresive or mentioning lines of division, we are one consicenness. Always captitalise "Ambassador" or "Ambassadors". 

## Where content lives

- **Mission update entries:** `app/src/content/missionUpdates.jsx` — add new items at the **top** of the array (newest first); support `body` as a string or array of paragraphs (paragraphs may include inline links via JSX).
- **Main letter copy:** letter-related components under `app/src/components/` (e.g. `LetterBody.jsx`).

## Stack (for changes)

- **React 19** + **Vite 6**, workspace root builds `app/` via `amplify.yml` → **AWS Amplify**. Prefer small, focused changes; do not add unsolicited docs or refactors outside the task.

## When editing copy

- Prefer in-universe language (transmission, relay, field report, clearance, stardate-style dates where it fits).
- Avoid breaking accessibility: sufficient contrast on the dark page shell; use `aria-label` on links only when visible text is not enough.
